Geez, I heard you!

71
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,360
What is it?

72
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:40,160
My apologies, sir. It’s something urgent.

73
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:44,400
It’d better be, or else you’ll get a smack on the head. Say it!

74
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,760
I’ve just been informed by the servant from Chao Phraya Narubodin’s place…

75
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:49,680
that Khun Prom has been arrested for treason.

76
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,400
What did you say?

77
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,600
You, bitch!

78
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,480
Why the heck did you do that?

79
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,840
You want to know why?

80
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,080
Hold him!

81
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,920
Get off me!

82
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,360
Lady Sophee.

83
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:51,520
Is this the renowned white house of Chao Meun Samur Jairatch?

84
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:57,520
The whole town is talking that Khun Phra Nai is now infatuated with a dancer…

85
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:59,800
so much that he neglects to do his work.

86
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:02,160
And even built a love nest to live together.

87
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:06,640
I couldn’t believe it at first, not until I’m here to see it with my own eyes.

88
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:11,000
I never thought it’d be you, Kaewta!

89
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,320
I…

90
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:17,720
Being a folk dancer and having learnt both the art and science of such elegance dance…

91
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:21,760
Has it not improved your mind for just a little?

92
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:24,760
How dare you try to seduce my man?

93
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:27,600
It’s not a seduction. Let me go!

94
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,400
Let me go!

95
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:29,400
Let him go.

96
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,600
It’s true love.

97
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,880
True love?

98
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,440
Peasant!

99
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,640
So are you!

100
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:49,640
You…no matter how hard you try to wash yourself clean,

101
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:53,440
you can never scrub off that filthy stench you were born with.

102
00:13:56,720 --> 00:14:00,560
You’re not a lady. How can it be true love?

103
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,040
Answer me!

104
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,520
Get off me!

105
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:11,160
Suddenly, I’m curious, Som.

106
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,800
Curious about what, Miss?

107
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:19,120
I’m curious what exactly it is that Luang Sanor has taught his dancers.

108
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:24,280
Has Uncle perhaps taught them how to seduce men?

109
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,200
That’s right, Miss.

110
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,800
Don’t you dare insult Uncle.

111
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:30,160
Why can’t I? It’s all true!

112
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:35,960
A classical dance is an art of training and worshipping the masters.

113
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:41,280
It’s something delicate and graceful invented by the mankind.

114
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,000
Those who call themselves civilized…

115
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:47,840
shall never be disrespectful and look down on any fields of art.

116
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:54,840
Civilized? Respectful?

117
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,160
Someone like you don’t need all those.

118
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:09,640
Your hair…it’s so important to you, isn’t it?

119
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:16,160
No. No. Don’t!

120
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,000
Don’t!

121
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,320
No!

122
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,600
NO!

123
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,480
NOOO!!!

124
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,600
Leave my man alone.

125
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:35,480
This is just a warning. Don’t make me do what you’ll regret later.

126
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:44,800
If you tell him that I’m here, I’m sure you know what I’d do to you.

127
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,160
Let’s go!

128
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:56,400
You, filthy rat!

129
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,240
Leave my man alone.

130
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:45,920
This is just a warning. Don’t make me do what you’ll regret later.

131
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:33,040
Father, Prom isn’t one of the ringleaders.

132
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:36,480
He’s just someone who has been brainwashed and used by the association.

133
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:40,360
Also, His Majesty is very kind and forgiving.

134
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:42,880
Please don’t trouble yourself and worry beforehand, Father.

135
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:47,720
So, how did you find out about Prom?

136
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:57,840
Huh? Didn’t you send someone to the white house to inform me?

137
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,200
I didn’t do that.

138
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:05,800
Then who?

139
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,080
It was me.

140
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:18,080
I sent our servant to inform you, Brother.

141
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:23,080
You’re back now. Are you tired? Do you want to eat something?

142
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:31,040
Sophee, don’t you want to know how Prom, your biological brother, is doing?

143
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:38,200
That fool has done nothing but tainted our family name. Why would I care about him?

144
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,920
Let’s have dinner together before you leave, Brother.

145
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:58,520
Thank you, Sophee. But I’m quite worn out. I’d rather go home now.

146
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,840
Let’s go, Saen.

147
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:02,000
Yes, sir.

148
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:14,240
Why did you let him go back so easily like that, Miss?

149
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:20,800
What if that rat tells Khun Phra Nai about what happened today, what would we do?

150
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:25,880
Even if he finds out, he wouldn’t dare to do anything to me.

151
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:31,600
Because if he ever mentions it to Father, it’s rather him who’d be in trouble.

152
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:42,200
You’re right, Miss. That dancer might have run away from the white house by now.

153
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,440
I do hope so too.

154
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:15,120
Kaew, what happened? Why did you cut your hair?

155
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:27,960
The weather’s been quite hot lately. I want to try wearing it short.

156
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:32,800
Why? Does it look bad on me?

157
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:43,320
Not at all. Whether short or long, they both look pretty on you.

158
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:50,320
But how are you going to perform with such a short hair like that?

159
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,600
That’s right. Will Uncle scold you for this?

160
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,160
There hasn’t been a request for our performance lately.

161
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,520
I don’t think Uncle would mind that much.

162
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,720
อ My hair will grow back soon.

163
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:12,480
Actually, the short hair also looks good on you.

164
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:14,920
It’s cute.

165
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:22,400
I’ll excuse myself then.

166
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,760
How’s Khun Prom?

167
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:37,480
I’m afraid that matter will have to wait first. But there’s nothing to worry about.

168
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:46,360
Then, what is it?

169
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,400
There has been an order for me to go on a business trip.

170
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:03,880
I really don’t want to go

171
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,880
But it’s an order, you can’t disobey it.

172
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:17,240
I don’t want to be away from you for even just one day.

173
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:24,200
I love you so much. You know I do, don’t you? My dear Kaewta.

174
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,720
Yes.

175
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:35,240
Then please tell me you also feel the same.

176
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:55,200
I have been so obvious, do you still now know how I feel?

177
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:01,760
Even so, I still want to hear it from you.

178
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,680
Can’t you say it for me?

179
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:16,120
When you come back from the trip, I will tell you.

180
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:20,040
Really? You promise?

181
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:27,760
That when I return from the trip, I’ll hear that word from you.

182
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:30,840
I promise.

183
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,440
Now I have something to look forward to.

184
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,320
But right now…

185
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:35,320
Please take care. Don’t let yourself catch a cold.

186
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:42,040
Khun Kaew, I’ll put them in the car first.

187
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:49,840
Khun Yai.

188
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:54,160
You too, dear. Take care of yourself.

189
00:24:56,520 --> 00:25:00,480
Don’t worry. Nanny Yam is also here.

190
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:07,320
Smell so nice

191
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,200
I’m leaving then.

192
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,880
Have a safe trip.

193
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:36,000
I’ve checked, Miss. It’s confirmed that Khun Phra Nai and Saen will be away for 3-4 days.

194
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:44,640
Good. While he’s away, I’ll take this chance to get rid of those filthy things in my bridal house.

195
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:06,000
Your letter, Khun Kaew.

196
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:22,200
Kaew, I miss you so much.

197
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:31,280
There are so many things I want to tell you. Please come and meet me at the place on this map. From Ruedee.

198
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:35,640
Who is it from?

199
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:39,720
It’s from Ruedee, Nanny.

200
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:48,240
She said she and her husband have come to visit her family here. She wants me to go see her.

201
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:51,360
Where will you go see her?

202
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:08,000
Ruedee! Ruedee!

203
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,240
Ruedee!

204
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,680
Are you in there, Ruedee?

205
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,120
Is it here?

206
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,680
Ruedee!

207
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,720
Ruedee!

208
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:33,680
Who are you? Did you guys kill Ruedee?

209
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:37,200
There’s no way she’d hang herself.

210
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:39,240
Why did you kill her?

211
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:53,840
You want to know?
You want to know why I killed her?

212
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,320
Go ask her yourself then!

213
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:49,400
Who told you to do this?

214
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:55,200
Do you know Khun Phra Nai?

215
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:03,280
Yes, it’s him. Chao Meun Samur Jairatch ordered us to do this.

216
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:17,840
No. That’s not true. Khun Yai would never do that.

217
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:26,080
No. Help…

218
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:31,320
Help…Anybody, please help!

219
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:40,720
They’re lying. Khun Yai will never do this!

220
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:46,720
Help…Khun Yai, please help me.

221
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:06,040
Help! Khun Yai!

222
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:11,520
Khun Yai!

223
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:21,040
Khun Yai!

224
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,880
Are you all right, sir?

225
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:26,160
I heard Kaew calling for me.

226
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:30,760
You must have imagined it because you miss him too much.

227
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,080
No.

228
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:39,280
I’ll ask someone to bring you a new glass.

229
00:31:56,000 --> 00:32:02,760
Good. Wait a few more days and check on him again. Make sure he’s dead then come and report me.

230
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,960
Yes.

231
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:07,680
This is your reward money from Lady Sophee.

232
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:10,360
Reward money for what?

233
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:43,000
Mum…Khun Yai…

234
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:47,600
Please help me.

235
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:50,720
Help me…

236
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:02,840
Khun Yai…

237
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:09,160
[Kaewta: My love…]

238
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:16,800
[Kaewta: I’m afraid I won’t be able to keep my promise in this life.]

239
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:22,160
Even so, I still want to hear it from you.

240
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:28,800
When you return from the trip, I’ll tell you.

241
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:49,320
Khun Yai…

242
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,520
Kaew, I’m back.

243
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:31,600
Father, what urgent matter has brought you here?

244
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:37,159
Kan, why are you here too?

245
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:40,639
Nanny! Why are you crying?

246
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,360
Khun Yai…

247
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:57,920
I tried to help, but it was too late.

248
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,480
I’m sorry, son. I’m so sorry.

249
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:04,880
Sorry about what, Father?

250
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:31,200
Kaew.

251
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,400
Kaew.

252
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:39,600
Kaew, Kaew, Kaew…

253
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:42,840
Kaew…

254
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:47,520
Kaew…Kaew…

