379
00:52:13,280 --> 00:52:15,600
Khun Kaew living up the happiness you’ve always dreamt of.

380
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:21,080
Saen.

381
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:24,960
Goodbye, Khun Yai.

382
00:52:25,160 --> 00:52:27,000
Should we be destined to meet again,

383
00:52:27,000 --> 00:52:28,320
I hope I’ll have a chance to

384
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:30,120
serve you again in the next life.

385
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:46,360
I hope we’ll meet again, Saen.

386
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,400
Where are you going?

387
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,840
Why are you…

388
00:53:29,200 --> 00:53:30,600
Are you feeling better now?

389
00:53:32,320 --> 00:53:35,280
Why are you here?

390
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:40,200
How did you create the white house’s floorplan…

391
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:44,840
when you hardly know the details of its structure?

392
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:48,480
Well, I…

393
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:49,320
I…

394
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:51,400
You’re avoiding my eye contact.

395
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:57,320
Is it because you’re afraid I might know?

396
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:01,240
That you’re not Ajarn Prem.

397
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:12,400
Is that right, Khun Yai?

398
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:30,360
Why are you trying hide it from me?

399
00:54:38,360 --> 00:54:41,360
Don’t you know how much I’ve missed you?

400
00:54:58,080 --> 00:55:00,520
I’ve missed you too.

401
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:09,080
Then, why are you leaving me again?

402
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:26,080
I’m sorry, my dear. I’ll never leave you again.

403
00:55:27,880 --> 00:55:29,800
Please don’t cry.

404
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:37,280
The reconstruction is already done. What are you thinking?

405
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:46,080
I still feel guilty about this body.

406
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:52,280
You mean Ajarn Prem’s body?

407
00:56:56,240 --> 00:56:56,800
Mhm.

408
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:02,240
He was a good man.

409
00:57:04,280 --> 00:57:07,200
Although his soul is probably in heaven by now,

410
00:57:10,360 --> 00:57:13,360
but I’ve taken possession of his body without his permission.

411
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:20,360
Even if it was for a justifiable reason, I still can’t help feeling guilty.

412
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:27,440
I understand you. But haven’t you also tried to leave this body so many times?

413
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:36,400
Also, you only did it to save my life.

414
00:57:40,400 --> 00:57:48,360
Maybe, having your soul in this body isn’t destiny...

415
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:56,360
But rather a chance to do good deeds…and make merits for Ajarn Prem.

416
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:10,200
You’re right. As long as I’m still alive in this body,

417
00:58:12,280 --> 00:58:17,400
I should use it to do good deeds, and dedicate those merits to Ajarn Prem.

418
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:22,280
That’s right.

419
00:58:27,320 --> 00:58:33,240
I was the cause of your death. I hereby vow to thee,

420
00:58:33,400 --> 00:58:40,360
should the next life exist, I shall dedicate it to pay back to you.

421
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:46,240
May you face only success and happiness in your next life.

422
00:58:53,240 --> 00:58:54,240
[Many years later]

423
00:59:16,240 --> 00:59:17,280
What are you thinking, dear?

424
00:59:21,240 --> 00:59:28,240
I’m just wondering…how long is eternity?

425
00:59:36,400 --> 00:59:38,280
If it means a lifetime

426
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:43,320
Then I hope it will happen in this life.

427
00:59:53,400 --> 00:59:55,360
But if it means something longer than that,

428
00:59:58,360 --> 00:59:59,360
I do hope I’ll always have you by my side like this.

429
01:00:13,400 --> 01:00:15,360
For me, eternity…

430
01:00:17,360 --> 01:00:19,240
isn’t something you can count with days,

431
01:00:19,360 --> 01:00:23,280
months, years, or even a lifetime.

432
01:00:26,200 --> 01:00:31,400
But rather with a heart, that’s never been wavered and always stayed true to you.

433
01:00:45,320 --> 01:00:47,240
I will love and stay by your side…

434
01:00:48,440 --> 01:00:50,360
until we’ve lost count of eternity.

